Motorists try and manoeuvre through traffic during a blackout. eNCA * Editor's note: This article is updated each time new information becomes available. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has implemented Stage 4 blackouts indefinitely. The power utility said it will publish a full statement in due course. READ: SA's Electricity Crisis | Power cuts cause business instability Stage 4 blackouts kicked in at 9am on Sunday morning. Eskom urged the public to continue using electricity sparingly. Stage 4 loadshedding will be implemented from 09:00 on Sunday morning - until further notice.
Eskom will publish a full statement in due course.